# Components Structure

The application's UI is built from these key components:

- [Layout.js](mdc:components/Layout.js): Main layout wrapper containing the sidebar and page content
- [Sidebar.js](mdc:components/Sidebar.js): Navigation sidebar with links to main sections
- [TransaksiForm.js](mdc:components/TransaksiForm.js): Form for creating and editing transactions
- [Modal.js](mdc:components/Modal.js): Reusable modal component used for forms and confirmations
- [Charts.js](mdc:components/Charts.js): Basic chart visualizations for financial data
- [AdvancedCharts.js](mdc:components/AdvancedCharts.js): More complex data visualizations
- [KpiCard.js](mdc:components/KpiCard.js): Key performance indicator display cards
- [Card.js](mdc:components/Card.js): General-purpose card component for content sections
- [FileImportExport.js](mdc:components/FileImportExport.js): Handles CSV import/export functionality

## Component Flow

Most pages follow this component hierarchy:
1. `_app.js` renders the `Layout` component
2. `Layout` contains the `Sidebar` and page content
3. Pages render specific components like `TransaksiForm`, `Charts` or data tables

